/* ============================================================
   DASHBOARD ECU — Board 2 — STM32F407 Discovery
   CAN Bus ECU Simulator — v5.0 PRODUCTION

   KEY CHANGES FROM v4.1:
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   1. CAN RX is INTERRUPT-DRIVEN (HAL_CAN_RxFifo0MsgPendingCallback)
      No polling in task — data arrives immediately via ISR
   2. ST7735_WriteString uses 5-argument signature:
        (x, y, string, color, bgcolor)
      All calls match this signature exactly.
   3. Floating-point → string: uses integer split (no %f)
      to avoid newlib-nano printf float issues on Cortex-M4
   4. "OVERTEMP!" status text rendered in RED on fault
   5. Partial redraws — only value areas cleared (no flicker)
   6. Buzzer: double-beep triggered ONCE on first fault RX
   7. Task names prefixed "User_Task_" (linker conflict safe)
   8. Temperature scale: raw CAN value ÷ 10 → float correctly

   HARDWARE:
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   ST7735 TFT (128×160):
     CS    → PA4  (GPIO Output)
     RESET → PA3  (GPIO Output)
     DC    → PB0  (GPIO Output) ← moved from PA2 to avoid USART2 conflict
     MOSI  → PA7  (SPI1 MOSI)
     SCK   → PA5  (SPI1 SCK)
     LED   → 3.3V

   CAN  : PD0=RX, PD1=TX (CAN1)
   UART : PA9=TX, PA10=RX (USART1) — PA2/PA3 freed for TFT DC/RST
   Buzzer: PE0 (GPIO Output)
   LED  : PD14 (Red, error)

   CUBEMX REQUIRED SETTINGS:
   ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
   SPI1  : Mode=TX Only Master, Prescaler=8, CPOL=Low,
           CPHA=1Edge, 8-bit, NSS=Disabled
           PA5=SCK, PA7=MOSI

   CAN1  : Prescaler=6, BS1=11, BS2=4, SJW=1 → 500kbps
           PD0=RX, PD1=TX
           Activate RX FIFO0 Pending Interrupt in NVIC

   USART1: 115200 8N1, PA9=TX, PA10=RX

   GPIO Outputs: PA3(RST), PA4(CS), PB0(DC), PE0(BUZ), PD14(LED)
   ============================================================ */

